<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-12-28T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-12-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="296" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d296">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">824.51/227: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cottrell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-12-28T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December 28,
                                        1923—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>27. Your 48, December 21, 9 a.m.</p>
                        <p>Department not impressed with the views of the President given in your
                            telegram.</p>
                        <p>You are requested to present in a formal note the views and protests of
                            the Equitable Trust Company as set forth in the Department’s telegram
                            No. 25, December 19, 6 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>